<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="698" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">151.10/1980a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-27T22:00:00-04:00">October 27,
                                1943—10 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1536. On October 21 House of Representatives by voice vote passed legislation
                        permitting immigration of Chinese into the United States on a quota basis
                        and allowing Chinese legally admitted to the United States for permanent
                        residence to become American citizens. See <pb facs="0796" n="786" xml:id="pg_786"/> Department’s 1468, October 12, 5 p.m.<note n="25" xml:id="d698fn25">Not printed.</note> Prospects appear good for early
                        action in the Senate.<note n="26" xml:id="d698fn26">On November 26, the
                            Senate passed by voice vote the act relating to immigration of Chinese
                            into the United States.</note>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>